attributes.magic: PE32+ executable (console) x86-64, for MS Windows

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The binary is the Windows SNMP Trap service (SNMPTRAP.EXE). It registers a service named 'SNMPTRAP' which listens for SNMP trap messages on multiple network protocols (IPv4, IPv6, IPX) on the standard SNMP trap port (UDP/162). It creates a named pipe `\\.\PIPE\MGMTAPI` to forward received trap data to local management applications. The observed behaviors, including service registration, network listening, and inter-process communication via named pipes, are all consistent with this legitimate Windows system component.
